		<td><b>Re: Armed For Battle - real time strategy for NES</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />One possibility is to use the variant of UNROM/UOROM that emulators implement, which is equivalent to this three-chip design: <ul><li>74161 to hold the bank number </li><li>7432 to make a fixed bank </li><li>7420 to decode SRAM (like Family BASIC) and avoid bus conflicts</li></ul>

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


